The paper focuses on neural networks and their architecture, specifically proposing a method for discovering neural wirings. This falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV), as the experiments are conducted on image classification tasks. The paper also discusses the use of neural architecture search (NAS), which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sparse neural network learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
